[
    {
        "content": "<p>I just had a random idea that feels like it could address a longstanding pain point in a way that feels natural to me:</p>\n<p>what if you could do this in module headers?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">exposes</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"nv\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">bar</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The problem this would solve is when I want to expose something named <code>foo</code> because <code>MyModule.foo</code> is the best name for it, but also I happen to want to name things <code>foo</code> inside my module a lot</p>",
        "id": 406777070,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1702047856
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so this would let me name the top level function <code>fooInternal</code> or something, and then expose it with <code>exposing [fooInternal as foo]</code></p>",
        "id": 406777261,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1702047924
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and then within the module I'd still be free to name things <code>foo</code> if I want to</p>",
        "id": 406777431,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1702047974
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Happened to me with <code>values</code> when writing the new dict impl</p>",
        "id": 406790014,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1702051647
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Cause there was already <code>Dict.values</code></p>",
        "id": 406790032,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1702051657
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I'm for this change</p>",
        "id": 406790090,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1702051678
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would this be allowed for imports too?</p>",
        "id": 406823410,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1702063016
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span> I think it already is? Or at least should be haha, possibly not implemented</p>",
        "id": 406834222,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1702067935
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I meant at the exposed name level:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>import Foo exposing [foo as bar]\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 406842865,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1702071948
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oh gotcha, yeah we should definitely support that!</p>",
